author: Nick Schwartz
title: Cristiano Ronaldo becomes Real Madrid's all-time leading scorer
text:
Cristiano Ronaldo becomes Real Madrid's all-time leading scorer USA Today Sports 23 hrs ago Nick Schwartz © AP Photo/Daniel Ochoa de Olza Real Madrid's Cristiano Ronaldo reacts during a Spanish La Liga soccer match between Real Madrid and Levante at the Santiago Bernabeu stadium in Madrid, Spain, Saturday, Oct. 17, 2015. Real Madrid beat Levante 3-0 at the Santiago Bernabéu Saturday, and Cristiano Ronaldo scored in the 30th minute to pass Raul as Real Madrid’s new all-time leading scorer. Ronaldo only came to Madrid from Manchester United in 2009, but in 310 career games has 324 goals for Los Blancos.
AdChoices Raul played for Real Madrid for 16 seasons, scoring 323 goals in 741 appearances.
Thanks team mates and Real Madrid fans for this beautiful moment. ❤️❤️❤️ pic.twitter.com/X2g9ZNwBim
